    <skos:definition xml:lang="en">class which serves as an identifier for a language. Each instance of the Language_Identification class represents a language as spoken (or written, signed or otherwise signalled) by human beings for communication of information to other human beings. Computer languages such as programming languages are explicitly excluded.
The identifier is comprised of the following parts, or attributes, which are based on IETF RFC 5646[33]. IETF RFC 5646 refers to these attributes as ‘language subtags’:</skos:definition>
