    <skos:scopeNote xml:lang="en">A quantity as defined here is a scalar. However, a vector or a tensor, the components of which are quantities, is also considered to be a quantity.</skos:scopeNote>
    <skos:scopeNote xml:lang="en">A reference can be a measurement unit, a measurement procedure, a reference material, or a combination of such</skos:scopeNote>
    <skos:scopeNote xml:lang="en">Symbols for quantities are given in the ISO 80000 and IEC 80000 series Quantities and units. The symbols for quantities are written in italics. A given symbol can indicate different quantities.</skos:scopeNote>
